The Executive Secretary of the Nigerian Christian Pilgrim Commission (NCPC), Rev. Dr Yakubu Pam has commended Pilgrims on good conduct as they are on Pilgrimage to Israel and Jordan. He made this statement recently during the JP ceremony of Pilgrims which was held at Amman, Jordan. Rev.Pam who was represented by the NCPC Director of Mobilization, Mr Christian Udegbunam, commended the fourth batch of pilgrims for being good ambassadors of Christ and Nigeria. He also commended the State Chairmen and Secretaries for their humility during the pilgrimage exercise, According to him,” history has been made by the Nigerian Christian Pilgrim Commission. He further reiterated that” we are privileged to be among the first set of pilgrims to make history while embarking on a pilgrimage to both Israel and Jordan “. Also speaking at the event was, His Royal Majesty, Ogunsanwo Olukayode, Oba Onilara Of Ilara expressed his appreciation to God for his mercies and the privilege to have such an experience so far. According to him,” We give God all the praise that we are able to come, see and conquer”.He explained that pilgrimage to the Holy land is not a jamboree but a spiritual exercise. The Chairman, Edo State Pilgrims Welfare Board and Chairman of Christian Association of Nigeria, Edo State, Bishop Oriname Oyonude Kure in his goodwill message, commended the Executive Secretary of the Nigerian Christian Pilgrim Commission for his vision. In his words, ” we are grateful to the able Executive Secretary of NCPC Rev. Dr Yakubu Pam for being a Visionary Man”. POLL He explained that Pilgrimage was in deep darkness due to the COVID-19 pandemic, but for the innovation of the Executive Secretary of NCPC, he was able to revive it. He appreciated all the State Governors for their support of pilgrimage in Nigeria. The fourth batch of pilgrims comprises pilgrims from Lagos, Oyo, Ogun, Ekiti, Osun and Edo states.